The paper deals with boosting algorithms, which are commonly studied in the machine learning community, and focuses on the restriction that the weak learners come from a class of bounded VC-dimension. This suggests that the paper is likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper mentions connections with Discrepancy theory, which is a topic in computational geometry, suggesting that it could also be categorized under cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The paper also explores the limits of the $\gamma$-VC dimension, which is a combinatorial-geometric parameter, indicating that it could be categorized under cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
